parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and shuddering can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and can also lead to premature wear of transmission components, resulting in costly repairs.

especially when accelerating or decelerating
the transmission slips or hesitates to engage
and the vehicle may jerk or lurch forward.

and the driver may experience difficulty shifting gears.
